gov.nasa.worldwind.symbology

Interface TacticalRoute

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AVList, Highlightable, Movable, Renderable, TacticalGraphic
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Route

    public interface TacticalRoute
extends TacticalGraphic
    An interface for tactical graphics that depict routes: a series of point graphics connected by lines. For example, the MIL-STD-2525 symbology set defines an Air Control Route that is composed of Air Control Points. The route is composed of many tactical graphics, but it is treated as a single graphic. If the route is highlighted all of the control points will also highlight, if the route is set invisible all the control points will be set invisible, etc.
    See Also:
    TacticalGraphicFactory.createRoute(String, Iterable, gov.nasa.worldwind.avlist.AVList)
